comments: All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Nurkic (POR) is late to establish himself in Smart's (BOS) path and delivers contact on the pick, which affects his ability to defend.

Pritchard (BOS) is established outside the restricted area when he absorbs the contact from Lillard (POR) and is dislodged from his defensive position. Fournier (BOS) has a resting forearm to Lillard's side and does not deliver any contact to push Lillard into Pritchard.
Lillard (POR) makes contact to Tatum's (BOS) arm on the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
During the drive, Lillard (POR) is established in Tatum's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact. Tatum does not go through Lillard at the end of the drive and the contact is marginal.
Nurkic (POR) jumps straight up as he absorbs the contact initiated by Tatum (BOS) jumping towards him and then makes clean ball contact to deflect the pass away.
Williams III (BOS) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs to Powell's (POR) leg, which does not affect his SQBR.

Williams III (BOS) extends his arm out on his block attempt and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Powell's (POR) head during his driving shot attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Lillard (POR) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage on the perimeter and the contact is marginal.
Brown (BOS) wraps Powell (POR) and affects his SQBR before any leg to leg contact with his teammate Tatum (BOS).
Anthony (POR) has a resting forearm to Langford's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs when he brushes his arm during his driving shot attempt.
Nesmith (BOS) commits a take foul on Lillard (POR).
Powell (POR) legally contests and cleanly blocks Pritchard's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
